reviewText: The video really wasn't what I was expecting out of a good nature show, too many people involved in it
Bought this for children...we found it very entertaining and learned a lot too.
Nature is great! Love the series!
I loved the monkeys in this documentary.  They are resourceful survivalists!
Another great NATURE story... well told & filmed

I adored this episode of Nature. Aside from stunning cinematography, when  the leader of a troop of toque macaques is killed, the troop all huddle on a branch above his body, eyes averted, holding each other and clearly grieving their loss. Even his old rivals now seem to show their deference, tenderly touching their fallen leader. I think monkeys grieve better than we do. This is television at its finest.

These human-like creatures are so well photographed in touching
situations. Unforgettable! The higher love and sincerity shines from them.
(Also check out Harold Klemp's book Animals are Soul Too. New possibilities
for us all.)
